In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki provided updates on several topics. President Biden joined a House Democratic Caucus meeting to discuss the American Rescue Plan, emphasizing the need to address the crises facing working families. Psaki also highlighted a meeting between President Biden and Senate Democratic leaders to discuss the status of legislative proceedings on the package. She outlined the differences between the President's plan and the plan proposed by 10 Republican senators. Psaki also addressed questions about the $1,400 direct payment, the reopening of schools, the Defense Production Act, the Space Force, and various foreign policy issues. Additionally, Psaki mentioned ongoing reviews of domestic violent extremism and the detention of American citizens in Russia. She confirmed that the President's goal is to administer 100 million COVID-19 vaccine doses in his first 100 days in office. Psaki also discussed voting access, the Mexico City Policy, and the President's position on unions and the middle class.